    "Layout": {}
  },
  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EYour content editors work hard. But a page that looks polished can still fail to communicate value, handle objections, or guide visitors to act. By the time your analytics catch it, the conversions are already gone.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EWhat the AI Page Evaluator does\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EOne click in the Umbraco content editor sends your page to an AI evaluator configured by your team. Within seconds, you get a structured report: which checks passed, which need attention, and specific suggestions \u2014 not generic AI prose.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EBuilt by ProWorks \u2014 Umbraco Platinum Partner with three MVPs on staff\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EProWorks has been building Umbraco solutions for over a decade, with clients including NASA, Microsoft, and Cal Fire. We hold three Umbraco MVPs on staff \u2014 among the most in any single firm globally \u2014 and are certified across every Umbraco LTS release from version 7 through 17. We built the AI Page Evaluator for our own clients first, then open-sourced it under the MIT license so every Umbraco team could benefit from it.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EThe numbers that matter\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELess than 2%\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 typical conversion rate when the value proposition is unclear or the CTA is vague, regardless of design quality.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E5\u201315%\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 conversion rate when copy is specific, proof-backed, and handles objections. Same audience, same traffic source.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E3\u20135 days\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 typical turnaround for a manual copy review from an agency or conversion specialist, per page.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E10 seconds\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 time to get a structured pass/fail report from the AI Page Evaluator.\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EWhat the evaluation covers\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EValue proposition clarity\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 can a first-time visitor understand the benefit in 5 seconds?\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpecificity and proof\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 are claims backed by concrete evidence, not vague assertions like \u2018trusted by thousands\u2019?\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObjection handling\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 does the page address why not a competitor, a DIY solution, or the status quo?\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECTA clarity and friction\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 is it obvious what happens when you click and how much effort it takes?\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMessage hierarchy\u003C/strong\u003E \u2014 do visitors read the most important information first, or do they have to hunt for it?\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Ch2\u003EFrequently asked questions\u003C/h2\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EDo I need a new AI subscription?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003ENo. The evaluator uses your existing Umbraco.AI profile \u2014 Anthropic, OpenAI, or any compatible provider. If you already have Umbraco.AI 1.8 configured, you are already connected. Token usage per evaluation is typically a few cents per page.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EHow complex is the setup?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EInstallation is one NuGet command: \u003Ccode\u003Edotnet add package ProWorks.Umbraco.AI.PageEvaluator\u003C/code\u003E. Configuration lives entirely inside Umbraco backoffice under Settings, AI Add-ons, Page Evaluator. No YAML files, no infrastructure changes, no deployment pipelines to update. Most teams evaluate their first page within 15 minutes of install.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EWill the feedback be specific or just generic AI prose?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EGeneric output is a prompt problem, not an AI problem. The Prompt Builder generates structured checklists from your document type properties. You define the criteria \u2014 clarity, SEO, tone, compliance, conversion \u2014 and the AI evaluates against those specific standards. The report returns specific pass/fail checks with plain-English explanations, not essays.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch3\u003EIs it really free?\u003C/h3\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EYes. MIT license. Open source on GitHub. ProWorks also offers a site-wide Content Evaluator service for organisations that want every page reviewed against a custom quality framework \u2014 contact us to learn more.\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
    </introText>
    <metaDescription>
      <Value><![CDATA[One-click AI evaluation inside the Umbraco editor. Get a structured pass/fail report on value proposition clarity, proof, objection handling, and CTA quality — before the page goes live.]]></Value>
    </metaDescription>
    <metaTitle>
      <Value><![CDATA[ProWorks AI Page Evaluator — AI Content Quality Checks Inside Umbraco]]></Value>
    </metaTitle>
